<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="247" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,778,1155,2092]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1192,1218]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is a combination of the Greek “ 
<emphasis box="[274,369,1228,1254]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">homalós</emphasis>
”, smooth, referring to the absence of longitudinal striae on its elytra, and “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", LeConte" authorityYear="1866" box="[624,733,1265,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Enchodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[624,733,1265,1291]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Enchodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, a presumably closely related genus. The name is feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="247" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,778,1155,2092]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">
The generic name 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte" authorityName=", LeConte" authorityYear="1866" box="[429,652,1374,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Enchodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[429,538,1374,1400]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Enchodes</emphasis>
LeConte
</taxonomicName>
has been sometimes mistakenly treated as masculine (
<emphasis box="[659,671,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">e</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[678,692,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">g</emphasis>
., 
<bibRefCitation author="Jung, B. H." pageId="1" pageNumber="247" refId="ref3517" refString="Jung, B. H. (2019) Insect fauna of Korea, Volume 12, Number 27: Tenebrionoidea - Arthropoda: Insecta: Coleoptera: Tenebrionoidea: Melandryidae &amp; Tetratomidae. National Institute of Biological Resources, Incheon, 85 pp." type="book" year="2019">Jung, 2019</bibRefCitation>
). According to Article 30.1.4.4 of ICZN (1999), “a compound genus-group name ending in the suffix - 
<emphasis box="[732,771,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">ites</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[145,204,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">oides</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[228,273,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">ides</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis box="[297,348,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">odes</emphasis>
, or - 
<emphasis box="[403,453,1521,1546]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">istes</emphasis>
is to be treated as masculine unless its author, when establishing the name, … treated it as such by combining it with an adjectival species-group name in another gender form”. When establishing genus 
<taxonomicName authority=", LeConte (1866)" authorityName=", LeConte" authorityYear="1866" box="[136,453,1665,1692]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Enchodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[136,245,1666,1692]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Enchodes</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="LeConte, J. L." box="[267,453,1665,1692]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" pagination="87 - 168" refId="ref3562" refString="LeConte, J. L. (1866) New species of North American Coleoptera. Prepared for the Smithsonian Institution. Part I. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 6 (167), 87 - 168. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 17758" type="journal article" year="1866">LeConte (1866)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
added a single previously described species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Haldeman" authorityName="Haldeman" box="[346,649,1702,1728]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Dircaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis box="[346,524,1703,1728]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Dircaea sericea</emphasis>
Haldeman
</taxonomicName>
, citing it as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Haldeman)" baseAuthorityName="Haldeman" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[136,478,1738,1764]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Enchodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis box="[136,333,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Enchodes sericea</emphasis>
(Haldeman)
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, the name should be feminine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="247" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,778,1155,2092]" lastBlockId="1.[810,1452,158,1228]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,312,1811,1837]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body relatively small, strongly elongate. Compound eyes coarsely facetted (
<figureCitation box="[529,651,1848,1874]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 2A, B</figureCitation>
). Antennae long, filiform. Maxillary palps simple (
<figureCitation box="[562,650,1884,1910]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Pronotum widest posteriorly, with somewhat produced posterior pronotal angles (
<figureCitation box="[332,424,1957,1983]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Prosternal process complete, gradually narrowed posteriorly, slightly extending beyond posterior procoxal margin (
<figureCitation box="[449,541,2030,2056]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Procoxae narrowly separated (
<figureCitation box="[263,358,2066,2092]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Protrochantins well exposed (
<figureCitation box="[732,848,158,2092]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Elytra without longitudinal striae (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1358,158,184]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). Meso- and metatibiae without transverse rows of bristles or spines (
<figureCitation box="[894,983,230,256]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Metatibial spurs normal-sized (distinctly shorter than half length of metatarsomere 1) (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1439,266,292]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Penultimate tarsomeres ventrally lobed in all three pairs of legs (
<figureCitation box="[900,992,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[136,235,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetId="figure-59@3.[165,1423,168,1675]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Head and prothorax, ventral view. B, Head and prothorax, dorsal view. C, Abdominal base and fore leg. D, Abdominal apex and metatibia, ventral view. E, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: an1–9, antennomeres 1–9; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; mstb, mesotibia; msts, mesotarsus; mtc, metacoxa; mttb, metatibia; mtv, metaventrite; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; pn, pronotum; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptcn, protrochantin; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820858" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820858/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Figs 2C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1003,1019,338,364]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[136,235,551,575]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,185,527]" captionTargetId="figure-191@4.[151,1436,185,527]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Details of Homalenchodes jarzembowskii Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai gen. et sp. nov., holotype, NIGP180475, under confocal microscopy. A, Mesotarsus, lateral view. B, Metatarsus, dorsal view. C, Metatarsus, ventral view. Abbreviations: mst1–5, mesotarsomeres 1–5; mtt1–4, metatarsomeres 1–4. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6820860" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6820860/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="247" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[810,1452,158,1228]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,979,374,400]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[987,1167,374,400]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Homalenchodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[987,1167,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Homalenchodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1859" box="[1311,1451,374,400]" class="Insecta" family="Synchroidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Synchroidae</taxonomicName>
a similar elongate habitus, lateral and oval eyes, and transverse head and pronotum. In fact, the adults of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1859" box="[810,950,482,508]" class="Insecta" family="Synchroidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Synchroidae</taxonomicName>
have an appearance similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1289,1447,482,508]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melandryidae</taxonomicName>
, but these two families are otherwise readily separable based on larval characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Crowson, R. A." box="[1107,1282,554,580]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" pagination="507 - 513" refId="ref3075" refString="Crowson, R. A. (1966) Observations on the constitution and subfamilies of the family Melandryidae (Coleoptera). Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 41, 507 - 513." type="journal article" year="1966">Crowson, 1966</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, synchroids are generally characterised by the long interfacetal setae (absent in 
<taxonomicName authority="Horn" authorityName="Horn" authorityYear="1888" box="[1145,1336,626,653]" class="Insecta" family="Synchroidae" genus="Mallodrya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1145,1263,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Mallodrya</emphasis>
Horn
</taxonomicName>
, although this genus might have been inappropriately placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lacordaire" authorityYear="1859" box="[810,950,698,724]" class="Insecta" family="Synchroidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Synchroidae</taxonomicName>
and needs to be further evaluated; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hsiao, Y. &amp; Konvicka, O. &amp; Ko, C. C." pageId="1" pageNumber="247" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref3459" refString="Hsiao, Y., Konvicka, O. &amp; Ko, C. C. (2018) The world fauna of Synchroidae Lacordaire, 1859 (Coleoptera, Tenebrionoidea, Synchroidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 407, 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2018.407" type="journal article" year="2018">
Hsiao 
<emphasis box="[810,866,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">et al</emphasis>
., 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), unmargined posterior edge of pronotum (distinctly margined in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Horn" authorityYear="1888" box="[1093,1211,770,796]" class="Insecta" family="Synchroidae" genus="Mallodrya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1093,1211,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Mallodrya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), prosternal process markedly extending beyond procoxae with long oval apex (prosternal process laminate, ending just before the posterior edges of procoxae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Horn" authorityYear="1888" box="[1259,1377,878,904]" class="Insecta" family="Synchroidae" genus="Mallodrya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1259,1377,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Mallodrya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and unlobed penultimate tarsomeres (
<bibRefCitation author="Slipinski, A. &amp; Lawrence, J. F." pageId="1" pageNumber="247" pagination="667 - 669" refId="ref4050" refString="Slipinski, A. &amp; Lawrence, J. F. (2010) Synchroidae Lacordaire, 1859. In: Leschen, R. A. B., Beutel, R. G., Lawrence, J. F. (Eds), Handbook of zoology, Arthropoda: Insecta, Coleoptera, beetles, Vol. 2: Morphology and systematics (Elateroidea, Bostrichiformia, Cucujiformia partim). Walter de Gruyter, Berlin, pp. 667 - 669. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / 9783110911213.667" type="book chapter" year="2010">Ślipiński &amp; Lawrence, 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hsiao, Y. &amp; Konvicka, O. &amp; Ko, C. C." box="[883,1093,950,977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" pagination="1 - 33" refId="ref3459" refString="Hsiao, Y., Konvicka, O. &amp; Ko, C. C. (2018) The world fauna of Synchroidae Lacordaire, 1859 (Coleoptera, Tenebrionoidea, Synchroidae). European Journal of Taxonomy, 407, 1 - 33. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2018.407" type="journal article" year="2018">
Hsiao 
<emphasis box="[958,1010,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">et al</emphasis>
., 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[1187,1367,950,976]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Homalenchodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1187,1367,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Homalenchodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has no interfacetal setae, a margined posterior edge of pronotum, a posteriorly gradually narrowed prosternal process with acute apex, slightly extending beyond posterior edges of procoxae, and lobed penultimate tarsomeres. Therefore, here we believe that it is appropriate to place 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Hsiao, Yoshitomi &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[810,990,1166,1192]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Homalenchodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[810,990,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="247">Homalenchodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the (currently non-monophyletic) family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[890,1049,1202,1228]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Melandryidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
